node.text:
I finally got the opportunity to track my McLaren 720s at Mosport, one of the most challenging (a lot of blind corners) and fastest circuits in North America! 

It was a phenomenal experience and the 720s impressed me even more with it's capability and proficiency on track.

This footage is completely recorded via the 720s' Track Telemetry and cameras (this is an extra option on the car which has 3 built in cameras for different perspectives). Glad I got this option indeed!

With that said, I have a few key areas to improve on at Mosport:

1) Braking - I was only using no more than 50% of braking/brake pressure (doh). I can definitely brake harder and thus later to get better entry while loading the front.

2) Throttle - Plenty of areas, especially the straight (has a curve) where I would either ease off the throttle or even coast it into the next corner, instead of being full throttle. 

I hope you enjoy the video!

node.title: Trackday At Mosport In My McLaren 720s

Unless a "trader" is able to show their account holdings and values (video), timestamped transactions, profit and loss statements, along with their name on all these, DO NOT believe a single word they have to say.

Please subscribe to the YouTube channel @RizInternational
